o create its portfolio ariel investment trust  ariel fund is an open ended equity mutual fund launched and managed by ariel investments llc the fund invests in the public equity markets of the united states it invests in stocks of companies operating across diversified sectors the fund primarily invests in value stocks of small cap and mid cap companies with a market capitalization between  billion and  billion it employs fundamental analysis by focusing on factors such as capital appreciation over time high barriers to entry sustainable competitive advantages predictable fundamentals that allow for doubledigit earnings growth skilled management teams and solid financials to create its portfolio the fund benchmarks the performance of its portfolio against the russell  value index russell  index and sp  index it employs proprietary research to create its portfolio the fund does not invest in corporations whose primary source of revenue is derived from the production or sale of tobacco products or the manufacture of handguns ariel investment trust  ariel fund was formed on november   and is domiciled in the united states detailed description  east randolph streetsuite chicago il united statesfounded in  phone  fax  wwwarielinvestmentscomaf key executives for ariel investment trust  ariel fund ms mellody louise hobson chairman chief executive officer and president age  mr tom herman cpa chief financial officer and treasurer age  ms anita m zagrodnik chief compliance officer vice president assistant secretary and assistant treasurer age  mr erik d ojala vice president and secretary age  ms merrillyn jean kosier vice president and trustee age  compensation as of fiscal year  similar private companies by industry company name region visory llc united states  road partners llc united states t partners llc united states jumpcom inc united states  ontario inc united states recent private companies transactions typedate target no transactions available in the past  months req